Compute the starting point of the provided line segment.



```js
segStart(tag: TagIdentifier) -> [number]
```


### Arguments

| Name | Type | Description | Required |
|----------|------|-------------|----------|
| `tag` | [`TagIdentifier`](/docs/kcl/types#tag-identifier) |  | Yes |

### Returns

`[number]` 


### Examples

```js
w = 15
cube = startSketchOn('XY')
  |> startProfileAt([0, 0], %)
  |> line([w, 0], %, $line1)
  |> line([0, w], %, $line2)
  |> line([-w, 0], %, $line3)
  |> line([0, -w], %, $line4)
  |> close(%)
  |> extrude(5, %)

fn cylinder(radius, tag) {
  return startSketchOn('XY')
    |> startProfileAt([0, 0], %)
    |> circle({
         radius = radius,
         center = segStart(tag)
       }, %)
    |> extrude(radius, %)
}

cylinder(1, line1)
cylinder(2, line2)
cylinder(3, line3)
cylinder(4, line4)
```
